http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Jaitely-to-be-chief-guest-at-Invest-Karnataka-2016/article13995663.ece

Finance Minister Arun Jaitley will be the chief guest at the inaugural ceremony of Invest Karnataka 2016, which begins on February 3. The government’s flagship event will also see participation from Union Ministers Nirmala Seetharaman, Nitin Gadkari, Suresh Prabhu, among others. The Congress government has also invited AICC vice-president Rahul Gandhi.When asked why Mr. Gandhi was invited for the event, Karnataka Industries Minister R.V. Deshpande said, “We are doing a global investors meet in which many Union Ministers and MPs are invited. Rahul Gandhi is an MP of the country.”Industry leaders Ratan Tata, Anil Ambani, Anand Mahindra, Sajjan Jindal, Kumar Mangalam Birla, among others, have also confirmed participation. The event will also have seven countries as partners — France, Japan, Sweden, South Korea, the U.K., Italy and Germany.As part of the event, the government has listed around 145 projects from various sectors like infrastructure, renewable energy, aviation and defence, biotechnology, and pharma for the investors, of which 48 are listed in Bengaluru and will be showcased at the event.“Infrastructure has to keep pace with development. We are a responsible government and under the leadership of the Chief Minister, we are trying to improve infrastructure in the city,” the Minister said, adding, “We are investing in smaller towns by providing adequate facilities required by the industry.”Infrastructure has to keep pace with development, says Industries Minister R.V. Deshpande